From: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2020 14:43:08 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/pm: fix ref count leak when pm_runtime_get_sync
 fails
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.8.6
Git-commit: 66429300e1bd9cdfbe96cfc475e4964db2a36921

[ Upstream commit 66429300e1bd9cdfbe96cfc475e4964db2a36921 ]

The call to pm_runtime_get_sync increments the counter even in case of
failure, leading to incorrect ref count.
In case of failure, decrement the ref count before returning.

